<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,326,534]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,362,389]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Known only from a few records along the east coast of New 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1090,363,389]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Guinea</collectingCountry>
in the Buna Bay area; dorsally yellowish to pale brown with black elytral apices. Most similar to 
<emphasis box="[891,1066,399,425]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
Aquil. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[965,1066,400,425]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Gilvainsula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="messoria" status="comb. nov.">messoria</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1073,1203,399,426]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1073,1196,399,425]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from which it is distinguished by the black elytral apices.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
